&gt; * Linux Red Hat AS 4
&gt;
&gt; On the following page I found something about problems while writing to
&gt; an NFS mount:
&gt; http://crawler.archive.org/articles/releasenotes.html#1_10_0_limitations 
&gt; &lt;http://crawler.archive.org/articles/releasenotes.html#1_10_0_limitations&gt;
&gt;
&gt; ----------------------------------------------------------
&gt; 1.2.1. java.io.IOException: No locks available
&gt; BDB-JE will complain &#39;No locks available&#39; when crawler is
&gt; being built/run on an NFS mount. Workaround is to locate
&gt; the &#39;state&#39; directory on a non-NFS-mounted volume.
&gt; ----------------------------------------------------------
&gt;
&gt; Might this be the problem: where can I find this excepion? I could not
&gt; find it in &quot;$HERITRIX_HOME/heritrix_out.log&quot;.
&gt;


























IIRC, exceptions showed in the UI in the list of alerts (and then 
probably in heritrix_out.log). 

Have you tried locating the Heritrix state on local disk?  Or is local 
disk too small?

Around here, a process is run to offload ARCs as crawl progresses.  
Would such a process work for you offloading ARCs and logs to the NFS mount?

